Description
-----------
DDSChatDemo is a command line chat application that allows users to exchange messages.

Command Line Arguments
-----------------------
argument: [user name]

Building Prerequisites
----------------------
The opensplice-idl-plugin and camel-dds component must be installed in the local maven repositories.

Building the demo
----------------
Open a command prompt and change directory to camel-dds-demo.
enter the following command: mvn install

Running the demo
-----------------
Start the Opensplice services.

Open a command prompt and change directory to camel-dds-demo. Enter the following command:

mvn exec:java -Dexec.mainClass=camel.dds.demo.DDSChatDemo -Dexec.args="user1"

Open another command prompt and enter the following command:

mvn exec:java -Dexec.mainClass=camel.dds.demo.DDSChatDemo -Dexec.args="user2"

Type a message on one of the terminals and hit <ENTER>. The message will appear on the other terminal.

Exiting the demo
-----------------
Type quit and <ENTER>
